but perhaps derived from the word in 1 above."]},{"name":"Alcott","meanings":["English: ostensibly a topographic name from any of a large number of places called in Old English as ‘the old cottage’ (Old English <i>(e)ald</i> + <i>cot(e)</i>). In fact, however, it is generally an altered form of   Alcock  , in part at least for euphemistic reasons.","History: Louisa May Alcott (1832–88), author of <i>Little Women</i> (1869), was the daughter of Amos Bronson Alcott (1799–1888), who had changed the surname from <i>Alcox</i>. The family trace their descent from an Alcocke family who emigrated from England to MA with John Winthrop (see   Winthrop  ) in 1630."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"John Alcock was born about 1362, in Cheshire, England, United Kingdom. He married Alice Elizabeth Alrich in 1386, in Cheshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died about 1389, in his hometown, at the age of 29."},"et":{"about 1362–about 1389":"umbes 1362–umbes 1389","1369–1399":"1369–1399","1386–1449":"1386–1449","1362–1389":"1362–1389","1369":"1369","1389":"1389","1399":"1399","1386":"1386","about 1389":"umbes 1389","1362":"1362","about 1362":"umbes 1362","1449":"1449","Ridge, Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","<Of, Badley, Suffolk, England>":"Badley, Suffolk, England"},"fi":{"about 1362–about 1389":"noin 1362–noin 1389","1369–1399":"1369–1399","1386–1449":"1386–1449","1362–1389":"1362–1389","1369":"1369","1389":"1389","1399":"1399","1386":"1386","about 1389":"noin 1389","1362":"1362","about 1362":"noin 1362","1449":"1449","Ridge, Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","<Of, Badley, Suffolk, England>":"Badley, Suffolk, England"},"fr":{"about 1362–about 1389":"environ 1362–environ 1389","1369–1399":"1369–1399","1386–1449":"1386–1449","1362–1389":"1362–1389","1369":"1369","1389":